# Canonical Universal Language Symbol Index (Copilot Migration)

## Purpose
Single, machine-readable source of truth for all UL symbols and their properties. Used for code generation, validation, and artifact/doc auto-generation.

## Format (JSON Array)
```json
[
  {
    "id": "point",
    "name": "Point",
    "meaning": "core, instance, origin",
    "geometric": "zero-dimensional, P ∈ ℝⁿ, μ(P)=0",
    "axiom": "point(x) ↔ x ∈ ℝⁿ ∧ μ(x)=0",
    "movement": "tap",
    "animation": "point_tap",
    "usage": ["focus", "start", "anchor"],
    "modality": "Core",
    "element": null,
    "cosmic_force": "Core",
    "phonetic": "pɔɪnt",
    "glyph": "•"
  }
  // ...more symbols
]
```

## Update Instructions
- Update this file only via migration scripts or Copilot-driven refactor.
- All code, tests, and docs must reference this as the canonical source.
